]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin framework incorporates safety‑monitoring components that continuously compare real‑time sensor data with model‑based predictions to determine whether the physical system is operating safely and optimally. When the monitors detect a safety or performance violation, they trigger alert mechanisms that allow either human operators or autonomous decision‑making algorithms to intervene and adjust the physical twin. Fault‑detection algorithms, among other diagnostic tools, are included as part of the safety validation process. "
